acy obliges its political leaders to respond to the expressed will of the people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDemocracyzUnited States. 0aPolitical participationzUnited States. 0aPublic opinion polls. 0aPublic opinionzUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : Democracy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Opinion. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aFishkin, James S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenovese, Michael A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenovese, Michael A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHeith, Diane J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Melinda S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Lawrence R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPinkus, Susan H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStreb, Matthew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStreb, Matthew J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTraugott, Michael W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWright, Gerald C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791485095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791485095/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles